reviewText:
SUITS BEST SHOW EVER !!!!!!!
All the actors are SWEET !!!!!!!
Waiting for next SEASON !!!!!!!
Just can't get enough SUITS !!!!!

This was very informative and I learned a lot about each character.  It was unremarkable to find out that "Harvey" was nothing like his character.  He seems to be shy and quieter than his character, but nonetheless spectacular.  Really love everything about Suits!

I always wondered if they had the figured out the can opener thing... now I know. I love that they all get along and I liked to hear from the creator how they come up with the law cases - what a great way to develop those cases - always looking at how it will affect the dynamics of the characters. This was very entertaining and I'm glad that I can be a fan of the who the actor's seem to be as people. Very funny!!!
Another great Paley panel! Got to see the personalities of the actors and how those filter through to the characters.
LOVE THE SHOW! ACTORS ARE AMAZING!
Our favorite series....great chemistry!!
5 STARS
Love watching Suits as well as their bloopers and events.
Love the show!!!

Patrick Adams was the most personable and natural talker of the group.  I was surprised that Gabriel Macht was considered the most different from his TV show character, w/ the director/writer chiming-in that Gabriel is the worse negotiator ever. Gina Torres seems in-charge even when just herself. And before watching this panel, I was bewitched by how cleverly and entertainingly Rick Hoffman plays Louis. But then Rick sat on stage, chomping on his gum like a cow, and that blew it. This is the second time I have seen an actor being interviewed like this (the other at an Apple store), where the actor is going-to-town on some gum.  It's unprofessional and tough to get past, as a viewer.  And he definitely couldn't field a question intelligently and chew gum at the same time...when it was his chance, he hemmed and hawed. More panels like this please - was entertaining to watch the ensemble's interactions and for them to share their observations.
Absolutely Great Show!
Love Suits! Great show, fascinating characters, wonderful actors, very interesting plot, unusually compatable cast.
Boring
Excellent .... fun
Realistic view of prominent attorneys, classy, shady, dramatic, rich, swag and scandalous.  Love it!
Was good having seen the show beforehand.  Good questions and answers.
Love love love the show
The cast and script are remarkable.  Best TV show ever.!!!

Absolutely loved it! Can't wait for the next season! It will be interesting to see if Rachel will move on or wait for Mike. Love those 2 together but I've read that Rachel moves on and finds someone new. Anyways, looking forward to watching the new season.
Loved it

This series has the most engrossing cast of characters, each one with their own fascinating personality. My family, friends & I "binged watched it & now can't wait for the new season to start. The acting is phenomenal & just so much fun to watch. Can't say enough great things about it.  Virginia LiCalsi Cohen
Fun insight into the dynamics of the cast of a great series, particularly relevant if you have only seen the first two seasons

I am such a big fan of suits. There are not a lot of TV series I love. But this crew is absolutely capture me. Patrick seems to have that likable persona. Meghan is so beautiful. Gina surprises me , I like her even more from watching this. I'm glad I finally watch this.
Suits is my favorite show by far! I love all the realistic relationships between the characters. Great writing and acting!
Great interview and I love the show.
It's always interesting to see & hear the actors talk about their roles.  Some good insight.
No words are descriptive enough to detail how good this series is.
Great show!
Loved it!
Love the show!
The BEST show ever
If you watch the series, this is great.
Love this show--can't wait till next season...

Very interesting and entertaining.  We really enjoy SUITS.  Got hooked the very first episode.
Hope they continue to create and offer the series.

Absolutely love this show!!! I as well signed up for Prime because of it! There are some movies, shows, etc. that even though u end up watching all season or shows and know the outcomes, you would watch over and over - like 24 (also a great series that I liked) - and would purchase. This for me is one of them not only because the writing is excellent and the acting, but the casting is perfect - 5 stars to these actors and actresses along with the creation, production and writing -- and Harvey is perfect as he is so faceted . Of course, Gabriel just is "so pretty" - can never tire of his person and style ! I hope this series goes on for well over 6 seasons!!  Thank you Amazon for carrying it!
Yes, Gabriel Macht is handsome!  (Joke from Palley Fest0.  :)  Interesting behind the scenes look at the actors, writers, creator.
Awesome!
Enjoyed it very much.
This is a great insight into a great show.
Awesome show!
Love it the cast are amazing!!
Great interview! Season 2 was the best!!
I love the cast. The personalities are so individual and unique, yet they make a perfect blend of a drama dey.  And they are all so darn good looking.
Oh Yes! addicted to the entire series! can't wait until next episode. Can be watched as a family routine. No major "R" moments.
Enjoying the revelations and learning just how similar the characters really are as they grow in character development
Loved it.  I like the whole cast.

I loved the "Suits: Cast and Creators Live at the Paley Center"! Being a fan of the show, the premise and the novelty of the show, and the cast, especially Gabriel Macht as Harvey Spector and Gina Torres as Jessica Pearson, I have watched this program many times, end still enjoy it. Thank you to the Paley Center for bringing us the Cast and the Creators of Suits, and thank you to the cast and the creators for creating such a great program. I hope there will be many many more seasons of Suits.
Love the characters and their re pore with each other.
I was unable to watch season 4 on my Amazon prime

Great fun to see the personalities of the cast with plenty of surprises and lots of fun. Suits is such a great show. Wish it could stay on for years. Love to binge watch this one.  Thank you Paleyfest for adding this dimension.
It was fun  to see the cast as themselves.

It was great to see them out of character, however I felt it was a big kiss butt session with the stars sucking up to writers, creator and each other, and all of them sucking up to the network people.
My son  recommended this show and he was right!  Cast is perfect, well written and perfectly sarcastic....love it!

Love that show...cannot wait for next season.
And then there's Harvey Spector.....move over Don Draper!

Never watched an actors' panel like this before but found it fun.

My favorite part is that apparently the actor who plays Louis Litt is truly awkward in a bizarrely compelling way. And surprisingly says 'like' and 'you know' more than most 14 yr old girls in his last answer.

Megan Markle reveals that she struggles to watch her scenes.

Overall the actors come across great, especially Gina Torres, even though she is pretty quiet. Patrick Adams has the most to say and is charming through and through.
A Great show!

Perfectly casted and cleverly written. This show is only for the grown and sexy. It's a great script and the delivery is witty  with a cynical sense of humor that I happen to love. Plus the fashion makes you want to work in an office. At least that office. And what can I say, Harvey Specter played by Gabriel Macht is so deliciously handsome and confident you'll start dreaming about him in your sleep.
This is a great show, with good charachters that fit well together. As long as it doesn't turn into a soap opera I'll keep watching.
Great behind the scenes content
Just loved seeing the cast love working with each other and respect the writing.  What a wonderful cast.
harvey is the sex pot of the country.  all cast members are just great actors.  wish there were more episodes during the season.
AN AWESOME SHOW........

My wife and I are fans of Suits and, when we found this show on Prime, thought it might be interesting.  It was.  It gives the viewer a glimpse of the real personalities of the main characters.  Some are quite different from the characters they play.

We, Very much enjoy the TV show Suits, and this was a hoot to watch! We enjoyed seeing the personalities "behind " the camera. We dread the season finale every year! But having worked in Film and Television in my past, I respect the need of "down time" i.e. hiatus.

Suits is a balance of humor and the seriousness of solving crimes.  But ultimately it is clean entertainment.  The directors do a great job meshing unique and flamboyant personalities with the more ordinary.  One of the things i love most is that the two main male characters as different as they are, are both smart and witty.  They pull their witt together to solve crimes.  Fun!
Tish
I liked it a lot... funny and well done. Got to understand a little bit of the "behind the seen" of this show. Interesting how different the actors are from their characters.

I just want to see the gif of Gabriel they talked about near the end?? Anybody knows?
Cute cast really!

I found it interesting and entertaining to see the creator's thinking as he develops each character and plot.  Also realized how good some actors really are and how others just play themselves. The camaraderie among the staff made it fun to watch. The writers of each episode are fantastic and so are the free ad lib wisdoms from the actors.

This show shows the life of attorney's - including the side all attorney jokes were derrived from, but also shows the humanity and political nature of playing the part.  The pairing of the two main stars is perfection.

You are all so cool, I can hardly wait for the new season and to see you all sitting together was so wonderful--your portrayal of real dramatic characters with real stories to tell, please continue without the foul language and nudity that you all have so aptly and discreetly dodged--an actual drama for adults and 'law' who would have ever guessed--hip hip hooray may you all have many, many great seasons together, your audience loves each and everyone of you and your writers, thank you so much!!!
Best show on TV.  Very different.  The interplay between actors is fantastic and the writing is extra special.  Just get the first season opening show and you are hooked.
Love this show, but what happened to it? It used to be on USA! Now, they want me to PAY for each episode! I find that seriously ridiculous! It is a good show, but REALLY?????
I love this show! The cast is great and the characters are well executed. Its entertaining. And the clothing featured on this show is stunning !!!

Interesting cast, good plot lines, although sometimes too clichd. Best when it focuses on the intrigues and manipulations within the firm and less interesting when  it becomes soap opera like dwelling on the characters personal lives.
Loved each and all the cast members!,
I love Suits. Thanks guys
It was great to see them as themselves and how the show came about and their parts.
Fast pace, good stories, good performance.
Everyone should watch this

awesome cast! great story!
thank you
Great Show!!!

It was great to see them as they are and learn some of the thing that went on in making the series. I kind of stumbled on this series and then I got addicted. I like the interactions, human traumas and dramas and their successes and failures and arrogance and humility. It is also cerebral and engaging
All characters were very engaging, great storyline.
Love the show....
